('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 1, 'multiple_choice', 'National Security', 'What company installed internet infrastructure at the White House in 2025?', 'Amazon', 'SpaceX (Starlink)', 'Microsoft', 'Google', 'SpaceX (Starlink)', 'This company is owned by Elon Musk and provides satellite internet service.', 'SpaceX installed Starlink satellite internet infrastructure at the White House in 2025. Starlink is SpaceX\'s satellite internet constellation that provides broadband internet access globally through a network of low Earth orbit satellites.', '["SpaceX", "Starlink", "satellite internet"]', '[{"name": "SpaceX Starlink Official Website", "url": "https://www.starlink.com/"}, {"name": "Federal Communications Commission - Starlink Authorization", "url": "https://www.fcc.gov/space-bureau/starlink"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Commercial Space Communications", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R46852"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 2, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'Who owns SpaceX and Starlink?', 'Jeff Bezos', 'Elon Musk', 'Bill Gates', 'Mark Zuckerberg', 'Elon Musk', 'This billionaire also owns Tesla and has advised the Trump administration.', 'Elon Musk owns SpaceX and its Starlink subsidiary. Musk has served as an advisor to the Trump administration while simultaneously providing critical communications infrastructure to the federal government, creating potential conflicts of interest between his advisory role and business interests.', '["Elon Musk", "SpaceX ownership", "business interests"]', '[{"name": "SpaceX Company Information", "url": "https://www.spacex.com/about/"}, {"name": "Securities and Exchange Commission - SpaceX Filings", "url": "https://www.sec.gov/edgar/browse/?CIK=0001181412"}, {"name": "Forbes - Elon Musk Profile", "url": "https://www.forbes.com/profile/elon-musk/"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 3, 'multiple_choice', 'Constitutional Law', 'What constitutional concern arises when presidential advisors\' companies provide government services?', 'Due Process violations', 'Conflicts of interest and potential corruption', 'Free Speech restrictions', 'Equal Protection violations', 'Conflicts of interest and potential corruption', 'Think about officials benefiting financially from their government positions.', 'When presidential advisors\' companies provide government services, it creates conflicts of interest that raise constitutional concerns about corruption and the faithful execution of laws. The Constitution\'s principles require officials to serve the public interest rather than their personal financial interests.', '["conflicts of interest", "corruption", "constitutional principles"]', '[{"name": "Office of Government Ethics - Conflict of Interest Laws", "url": "https://www.oge.gov/Web/oge.nsf/Resources/Conflicts+of+Interest"}, {"name": "Supreme Court - McDonnell v. United States", "url": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/579/15-474/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Executive Branch Ethics", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R43186"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 4, 'multiple_choice', 'National Security', 'What security risks exist when private companies control government communications?', 'No security risks exist', 'Potential surveillance, data breaches, and foreign influence', 'Only financial risks', 'Improved security through private sector', 'Potential surveillance, data breaches, and foreign influence', 'Private control creates vulnerabilities that don\'t exist with government-controlled systems.', 'Private companies controlling government communications create security risks including potential corporate surveillance of government data, vulnerability to data breaches exposing classified information, and potential foreign influence through corporate partnerships or investments that could compromise national security.', '["security risks", "private control", "government communications"]', '[{"name": "National Institute of Standards and Technology - Cybersecurity Framework", "url": "https://www.nist.gov/cyberframework"}, {"name": "Government Accountability Office - Federal Cybersecurity", "url": "https://www.gao.gov/products/gao-22-104707"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Government Communications Security", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R46554"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 5, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'What federal process typically governs major government technology contracts?', 'Direct purchase without oversight', 'Competitive bidding through established procurement procedures', 'Presidential discretion only', 'Congressional approval required', 'Competitive bidding through established procurement procedures', 'Federal contracting follows established rules to ensure fairness and best value.', 'Major government technology contracts typically follow competitive bidding procedures governed by the Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR), which requires open competition, transparent evaluation criteria, and documentation to ensure fair competition and best value for taxpayers.', '["federal procurement", "competitive bidding", "Federal Acquisition Regulation"]', '[{"name": "General Services Administration - Federal Acquisition Regulation", "url": "https://www.acquisition.gov/far/"}, {"name": "Government Accountability Office - Federal Contracting", "url": "https://www.gao.gov/products/gao-19-196"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Federal Procurement Process", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R40516"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 6, 'multiple_choice', 'National Security', 'What agency typically oversees White House communications security?', 'FBI', 'Secret Service and White House Communications Agency', 'CIA', 'NSA exclusively', 'Secret Service and White House Communications Agency', 'These agencies specialize in presidential protection and secure communications.', 'The Secret Service and White House Communications Agency typically oversee White House communications security. The Secret Service handles presidential protection including secure facilities, while WHCA manages secure communications systems and protocols for presidential communications.', '["Secret Service", "White House Communications Agency", "presidential security"]', '[{"name": "Secret Service - Protective Mission", "url": "https://www.secretservice.gov/protection/"}, {"name": "White House Communications Agency Information", "url": "https://www.defense.gov/News/Feature-Stories/Story/Article/2509317/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Presidential Security", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R44551"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 7, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'What oversight mechanisms exist for government technology contracts?', 'No oversight exists', 'Congressional oversight, GAO audits, and inspector general reviews', 'Only media oversight', 'Corporate self-regulation only', 'Congressional oversight, GAO audits, and inspector general reviews', 'Multiple government institutions provide checks and balances.', 'Government technology contracts are subject to multiple oversight mechanisms including congressional committee oversight, Government Accountability Office audits, inspector general reviews, and public disclosure requirements that ensure accountability and compliance with federal procurement regulations.', '["government oversight", "GAO audits", "inspector general reviews"]', '[{"name": "Government Accountability Office - Contracting Oversight", "url": "https://www.gao.gov/about/what-gao-does/government-contracting"}, {"name": "Council of Inspectors General", "url": "https://www.ignet.gov/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Federal Oversight", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R45442"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 8, 'multiple_choice', 'Constitutional Law', 'What constitutional principle requires government officials to avoid conflicts of interest?', 'Separation of Powers', 'Faithful execution of laws and public trust', 'Federalism', 'Judicial Review', 'Faithful execution of laws and public trust', 'Officials must faithfully execute their duties without personal financial influence.', 'The constitutional principle requiring faithful execution of laws and maintenance of public trust requires government officials to avoid conflicts of interest. This ensures that officials make decisions based on public interest rather than personal financial gain, preserving democratic governance integrity.', '["faithful execution", "public trust", "constitutional duty"]', '[{"name": "Constitution Annotated - Take Care Clause", "url": "https://constitution.congress.gov/browse/essay/artII-S3-1/"}, {"name": "Office of Government Ethics - Constitutional Basis", "url": "https://www.oge.gov/Web/oge.nsf/Resources/Constitutional+Foundation"}, {"name": "Supreme Court - Public Trust Doctrine", "url": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/corruption-cases/"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 9, 'multiple_choice', 'National Security', 'How does satellite internet differ from traditional internet in terms of security?', 'Satellite internet is always more secure', 'Satellite internet has different vulnerabilities including space-based threats', 'No security differences exist', 'Traditional internet is always less secure', 'Satellite internet has different vulnerabilities including space-based threats', 'Space-based systems face unique security challenges.', 'Satellite internet has different security vulnerabilities than traditional internet, including potential attacks on satellite infrastructure in space, radio frequency interference, and challenges in encrypting satellite communications. These space-based threats require specialized security measures.', '["satellite security", "space-based threats", "communication vulnerabilities"]', '[{"name": "National Institute of Standards and Technology - Satellite Security", "url": "https://www.nist.gov/programs-projects/satellite-cybersecurity"}, {"name": "Department of Defense - Space Security", "url": "https://www.defense.gov/News/Releases/Release/space-security/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Satellite Infrastructure Security", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R46852"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 10, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'What role does the General Services Administration play in federal technology procurement?', 'No role in technology procurement', 'Manages federal procurement policies and contracts', 'Only handles real estate', 'Provides security clearances', 'Manages federal procurement policies and contracts', 'GSA is the federal government\'s central procurement agency.', 'The General Services Administration manages federal procurement policies and contracts, including technology purchases for government agencies. GSA establishes acquisition rules, negotiates government-wide contracts, and ensures compliance with federal procurement regulations.', '["General Services Administration", "federal procurement", "technology contracts"]', '[{"name": "General Services Administration Official Website", "url": "https://www.gsa.gov/"}, {"name": "GSA - Federal Acquisition Service", "url": "https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/organization/federal-acquisition-service"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - GSA Role", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R40516"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 11, 'multiple_choice', 'National Security', 'What concerns exist about foreign access to U.S. satellite communications?', 'No foreign access concerns exist', 'Potential espionage, signal interception, and cyber attacks', 'Only economic competition concerns', 'Improved international cooperation', 'Potential espionage, signal interception, and cyber attacks', 'Foreign actors may target satellite communications for intelligence gathering.', 'Foreign access to U.S. satellite communications raises concerns about espionage through signal interception, cyber attacks on satellite infrastructure, and potential foreign intelligence gathering from intercepted government communications, requiring robust security measures and oversight.', '["foreign espionage", "signal interception", "cyber attacks"]', '[{"name": "National Security Agency - Communications Security", "url": "https://www.nsa.gov/What-We-Do/Cybersecurity/"}, {"name": "Department of Homeland Security - Critical Infrastructure", "url": "https://www.cisa.gov/topics/critical-infrastructure-security-and-resilience"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Foreign Intelligence Threats", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R46554"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 12, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'What transparency requirements exist for government contracts?', 'All contracts are classified', 'Public disclosure through databases like FPDS and USAspending.gov', 'No transparency requirements', 'Only congressional access', 'Public disclosure through databases like FPDS and USAspending.gov', 'Government contracting information is generally public to ensure accountability.', 'Government contracts are subject to transparency requirements including public disclosure through databases like the Federal Procurement Data System (FPDS) and USAspending.gov, which allow citizens to track federal spending and contractor performance.', '["contract transparency", "public disclosure", "government accountability"]', '[{"name": "USAspending.gov - Federal Spending Database", "url": "https://www.usaspending.gov/"}, {"name": "Federal Procurement Data System", "url": "https://www.fpds.gov/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Contract Transparency", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R40516"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 13, 'multiple_choice', 'Constitutional Law', 'How do presidential conflicts of interest affect separation of powers?', 'They strengthen separation of powers', 'They can undermine checks and balances by creating competing loyalties', 'They have no effect on separation of powers', 'They only affect the judicial branch', 'They can undermine checks and balances by creating competing loyalties', 'Conflicts create competing loyalties that weaken democratic oversight.', 'Presidential conflicts of interest can undermine separation of powers by creating competing loyalties between public duties and private interests, weakening the system of checks and balances that requires officials to act solely in the public interest for democratic accountability to function properly.', '["separation of powers", "checks and balances", "competing loyalties"]', '[{"name": "Congressional Research Service - Separation of Powers", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R42733"}, {"name": "Supreme Court - Separation of Powers Cases", "url": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/separation-of-powers/"}, {"name": "Federalist Papers - Separation of Powers Analysis", "url": "https://guides.loc.gov/federalist-papers/separation-of-powers"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 14, 'multiple_choice', 'National Security', 'What classification levels might apply to White House communications?', 'Only public information', 'Unclassified through Top Secret and special access programs', 'Only confidential level', 'No classification applies', 'Unclassified through Top Secret and special access programs', 'Presidential communications cover the full range of classification levels.', 'White House communications span all classification levels from unclassified public information through Top Secret and special access programs for the most sensitive national security information. This requires communications systems with appropriate security measures for each classification level.', '["classification levels", "Top Secret", "special access programs"]', '[{"name": "Executive Order 13526 - Classified National Security Information", "url": "https://www.archives.gov/isoo/policy-documents/cnsi-eo.html"}, {"name": "National Archives - Classification Standards", "url": "https://www.archives.gov/isoo"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Information Classification", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R41528"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 15, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'What federal law governs conflicts of interest for executive branch officials?', 'Federal Election Campaign Act', '18 USC 208 and related ethics laws', 'Administrative Procedure Act', 'Government in the Sunshine Act', '18 USC 208 and related ethics laws', 'This criminal statute specifically addresses financial conflicts of interest.', '18 USC 208 and related federal ethics laws govern conflicts of interest for executive branch officials, prohibiting participation in matters that could financially benefit the official or their business interests. Violations can result in criminal prosecution and removal from office.', '["18 USC 208", "ethics laws", "conflicts of interest"]', '[{"name": "18 USC 208 - Criminal Conflict of Interest Statute", "url": "https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2011-title18/pdf/USCODE-2011-title18-partI-chap11-sec208.pdf"}, {"name": "Office of Government Ethics - Conflict Laws", "url": "https://www.oge.gov/Web/oge.nsf/Resources/Criminal+Conflict+of+Interest+Statutes"}, {"name": "Department of Justice - Public Integrity Section", "url": "https://www.justice.gov/criminal/pin"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 16, 'multiple_choice', 'National Security', 'How does dependence on private companies affect national security planning?', 'It improves national security planning', 'It creates vulnerabilities and reduces government control', 'It has no effect on security planning', 'It only affects military operations', 'It creates vulnerabilities and reduces government control', 'Private dependence can limit government options during crises.', 'Dependence on private companies for critical infrastructure creates national security vulnerabilities by reducing government control over essential systems, creating single points of failure, and potentially limiting government options during national emergencies or conflicts with private contractors.', '["private dependence", "government control", "critical infrastructure"]', '[{"name": "Department of Homeland Security - Critical Infrastructure Strategy", "url": "https://www.cisa.gov/topics/critical-infrastructure-security-and-resilience"}, {"name": "Government Accountability Office - Critical Infrastructure Protection", "url": "https://www.gao.gov/products/gao-22-104727"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Infrastructure Security", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R46554"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 17, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'What congressional committees have oversight jurisdiction over government procurement?', 'No congressional oversight exists', 'Government Operations, Armed Services, and Appropriations committees', 'Only Ethics committees', 'State legislature committees', 'Government Operations, Armed Services, and Appropriations committees', 'Multiple committees have different aspects of procurement oversight.', 'Congressional oversight of government procurement involves multiple committees including Government Operations (oversight of procurement policies), Armed Services (defense contracts), and Appropriations committees (budget oversight), each providing different aspects of accountability and oversight.', '["congressional oversight", "committee jurisdiction", "procurement oversight"]', '[{"name": "House Oversight Committee", "url": "https://oversight.house.gov/"}, {"name": "Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs", "url": "https://www.hsgac.senate.gov/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Committee Oversight", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R45442"}]'),

