('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 23, 'short_answer', 'National Security', 'What company installed satellite internet infrastructure at the White House in 2025?', '', '', '', '', 'SpaceX', 'This company owns the Starlink satellite internet service.', 'SpaceX installed Starlink satellite internet infrastructure at the White House in 2025. SpaceX is Elon Musk\'s space company that operates the Starlink constellation providing global satellite internet coverage.', '["SpaceX", "Starlink", "satellite internet"]', '[{"name": "SpaceX Official Website", "url": "https://www.spacex.com/"}, {"name": "Starlink Service Information", "url": "https://www.starlink.com/"}, {"name": "Federal Communications Commission - Starlink", "url": "https://www.fcc.gov/space-bureau/starlink"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 24, 'short_answer', 'Constitutional Law', 'What federal criminal statute governs conflicts of interest for executive branch officials?', '', '', '', '', '18 USC 208', 'This criminal law specifically prohibits officials from participating in matters affecting their financial interests.', '18 USC 208 governs conflicts of interest for executive branch officials. This criminal statute prohibits federal officials from participating in any matter in which they have a financial interest, including matters affecting their business investments or companies.', '["18 USC 208", "criminal statute", "conflict of interest"]', '[{"name": "18 USC 208 - Criminal Conflict of Interest Statute", "url": "https://www.govinfo.gov/content/pkg/USCODE-2011-title18/pdf/USCODE-2011-title18-partI-chap11-sec208.pdf"}, {"name": "Office of Government Ethics - Criminal Statutes", "url": "https://www.oge.gov/Web/oge.nsf/Resources/Criminal+Conflict+of+Interest+Statutes"}, {"name": "Department of Justice - Ethics Enforcement", "url": "https://www.justice.gov/criminal/pin"}]'),

('2025-03-15-starlink-white-house-install', 25, 'short_answer', 'Government', 'What federal agency typically manages government-wide procurement policies and major technology contracts?', '', '', '', '', 'General Services Administration', 'This agency serves as the federal government\'s central procurement and property management organization.', 'The General Services Administration (GSA) typically manages government-wide procurement policies and major technology contracts. GSA establishes acquisition rules, negotiates enterprise-wide contracts, and ensures compliance with federal procurement regulations across government agencies.', '["General Services Administration", "GSA", "federal procurement"]', '[{"name": "General Services Administration", "url": "https://www.gsa.gov/"}, {"name": "GSA Federal Acquisition Service", "url": "https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/organization/federal-acquisition-service"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - GSA Role", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R40516"}]');